The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech on April 19, 2017, at the Yokosuka Naval Base in Yokosuka City, Japan. He praised the service and dedication of the American and Japanese military personnel stationed there and expressed gratitude on behalf of President Donald Trump. Pence emphasized the importance of the United States-Japan alliance as the cornerstone of peace, prosperity, and freedom in the Asia Pacific region. He highlighted the commitment of the United States to strengthen its presence in the region and praised the USS Ronald Reagan, which symbolizes the ironclad alliance between the two countries. Pence also addressed the threat posed by North Korea and reaffirmed the United States' commitment to defend its allies and protect its interests. He assured the audience that all options are on the table and that the United States will respond with overwhelming force if attacked. Pence concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the future and the United States' commitment to security and prosperity in the Asia Pacific.